1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Your alarm isn't the problem.
Your light exposure is.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Waking up is hard. Every morning
feels the same. Heavy. Slow. Painful.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Your body wakes up to LIGHT, not sound. Indoor morning light is 50-100 lux. Outside,
even cloudy, is 2,000-10,000 lux. Your brain needs the bright signal to fully wake up.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
First thing after waking: step outside. 10 minutes. Don't look
at your phone first — look at the sky.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Link in bio — free
energy profile in 30 seconds.

